                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/24/2003&nbsp;: 1:46:04 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> I don't consider myself uber, but I have found a few ways to improve the odds of getting more groups in a post lvl 60 environment.  <br /><br />1.  Get fast acting group friendly DoT's.  Namely, FP and SK.  I just got BoT last night, and I'm sure that will help.<br /><br />2.  Improve you DD output.  I have Fury of Magic 2 which seems to yield a critical hit every 6 or 7th time.  Also, I further stack the deck in my favor by getting summoned items like the wrist item.  You would be amazed at how many people notice a 3k neurotoxin.<br /><br />3.  Don't loot the small stuff.  You can always farm.  Let your poorer cousins loot more.  You are after bigger fish anyway.<br /><br />4.  Don't die; FD and then help with corpse retrieval.  Also, reduce downtime by twitching upon their rez.  (Generates a great deal of goodwill.)<br /><br />I'm sure there are many more tricks.  Think I might start a thread.<br /><br />Mortia</span></font></td>
